other_tests.procedure_name: Endoscopic removal of stone(s) from biliary tract

other_tests.findings: The pancreas enhances homogeneously. No signs of pancreatic necrosis are noted. Peripancreatic fluid collection within the anterior pararenal space with extension into the left paracolic gutter. There is diffuse thickening of the second, third, and fourth portion of the duodenum and ileus involving the proximal small bowel loops. Moderate amount of ascites noted within the anterior abdominal wall. Diffuse mesenteric haziness and nodularity noted in the left upper quadrant area.
